	<h2>Spreading Grounds</h2>
	<img style="width: 100%" src='/img/grounds1.jpg' align="left"/>
	<img style="width: 100%" src='/img/grounds2.jpg' align="left"/>

      </div>
      
      <ul class="col offset-l1 l6 m6 s12">
	<li>The use of spreading grounds adjacent to river channels and in soft-bottom channels permits water to percolate into groundwater basins for later pumping to conserve the maximum possible amount of storm water and other waters. These groundwater recharge facilities are located in areas where the underlying soils are composed of permeable formations and in hydraulic connection with the underlying aquifer. About 30 to 40 percent of the water used in the County is pumped from groundwater supplies. </li>
      </ul>
